The defendant Paul A. Street Jr. was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 1:33pm [mo]
Defendant Paul A. Street in court, in custody with Attorney Jeffrey Jacob De La Rosa.   ADA Jeffrey Shock appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " NO CONTEST " entered; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

ADA Shock submits victim impact statement
Sentencing arguments given by Counsel

The Court sentences Defendant to:
--serve 7 months in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges; this is to be served consecutive to sentence in being
--this sentence can be transferred to any other county so long as it is served as it would be in Jefferson County and at no additional cost to Jefferson County
--3 days credit for time already served given

--the Court orders restitution in the amount of $350.61 to Wildes Construction LLC., to be converted to civil judgment
--all court costs and fees are to be converted to civil judgment

The Court directs the Clerk to apply any cash bond posted and return remainder(if any) to surety.
DNA is not ordered due to date of violation
